00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:26.630 align:middle line:84%
>>GREGG BRADEN: Hello,
my name is Gregg Braden.

00:00:26.630 --> 00:00:29.030 align:middle line:10%
I'd like to welcome you to
this all-new presentation

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:32.689 align:middle line:10%
of "The Divine Matrix"
bridging time, space, miracles,

00:00:32.689 --> 00:00:34.010 align:middle line:10%
and belief.

00:00:34.010 --> 00:00:36.000 align:middle line:84%
In the last episode
of this program,

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.760 align:middle line:84%
we saw how a 3,000-year-old
map of time holds the key

00:00:40.760 --> 00:00:43.490 align:middle line:84%
to what's possible in the
world as well as our lives.

00:00:43.490 --> 00:00:46.970 align:middle line:84%
In this episode, we'll cross
the traditional boundaries

00:00:46.970 --> 00:00:49.790 align:middle line:84%
that separate the physics
and biology in the past

00:00:49.790 --> 00:00:53.300 align:middle line:84%
to reveal the superhuman
potential of what is now being

00:00:53.300 --> 00:00:56.480 align:middle line:84%
recognized as an
internal technology

00:00:56.480 --> 00:00:59.450 align:middle line:84%
and how we can use our
inner technology to bypass,

00:00:59.450 --> 00:01:02.780 align:middle line:84%
to hack the limits of what we
believe was possible for us

00:01:02.780 --> 00:01:04.426 align:middle line:90%
in the past.

00:01:04.426 --> 00:01:09.080 align:middle line:84%
A new school of thought suggests
that consciousness informs

00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:13.650 align:middle line:84%
itself through its creation,
through its art, music, books,

00:01:13.650 --> 00:01:15.140 align:middle line:90%
and movies.

00:01:15.140 --> 00:01:17.030 align:middle line:84%
With this idea in
mind, when we look

00:01:17.030 --> 00:01:19.820 align:middle line:84%
at the themes of some of
the most popular movies

00:01:19.820 --> 00:01:22.070 align:middle line:84%
of our time, what
are those movies

00:01:22.070 --> 00:01:23.630 align:middle line:90%
telling us about ourselves?

00:01:23.630 --> 00:01:27.140 align:middle line:84%
If consciousness is
informing us of something

00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:30.560 align:middle line:84%
that we need to know about
ourselves through the things

00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:33.920 align:middle line:84%
that we create to remind
ourselves of ourselves,

00:01:33.920 --> 00:01:36.050 align:middle line:90%
what are those films telling us?

00:01:36.050 --> 00:01:39.140 align:middle line:10%
Well, examples include
the hugely popular movies

00:01:39.140 --> 00:01:41.300 align:middle line:10%
like "The Matrix," for
example, or "Avatar,"

00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:43.550 align:middle line:10%
or the movie "Inception."

00:01:43.550 --> 00:01:45.740 align:middle line:84%
What are films like
these saying to us?

00:01:45.740 --> 00:01:49.400 align:middle line:84%
What part of our reality
are they reminding us of?

00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:52.400 align:middle line:84%
Well, if we look at the common
themes, they'll give us a clue.

00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:54.560 align:middle line:84%
As different as they
are from one another,

00:01:54.560 --> 00:01:57.340 align:middle line:84%
each of these movies is
suggesting, number one,

00:01:57.340 --> 00:02:01.460 align:middle line:84%
that there is a world that
exists we simply cannot see

00:02:01.460 --> 00:02:03.740 align:middle line:90%
from our limited perspective.

00:02:03.740 --> 00:02:07.250 align:middle line:84%
But this world influences
our everyday lives.

00:02:07.250 --> 00:02:11.870 align:middle line:84%
Number two, we're told that
we're limited in our lives

00:02:11.870 --> 00:02:15.140 align:middle line:84%
only until we wake
up to the parameters

00:02:15.140 --> 00:02:16.910 align:middle line:90%
of this unseen world.

00:02:16.910 --> 00:02:20.900 align:middle line:84%
Number three, they're telling
us that everyone has the ability

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:24.140 align:middle line:84%
to do just that, to
wake up and to transcend

00:02:24.140 --> 00:02:27.200 align:middle line:84%
the limits of their
lives that begin

00:02:27.200 --> 00:02:29.870 align:middle line:84%
with the events in the world
that we can't even see.

00:02:29.870 --> 00:02:34.070 align:middle line:10%
The success of a recent movie--
the 2017 movie "Arrival--"

00:02:34.070 --> 00:02:37.190 align:middle line:10%
is another beautiful
example of what I mean here.

00:02:37.190 --> 00:02:39.710 align:middle line:10%
And it opens the door
to precisely what I want

00:02:39.710 --> 00:02:41.840 align:middle line:10%
to talk about in this episode.

00:02:41.840 --> 00:02:45.280 align:middle line:10%
The theme of the
"Arrival" is so powerful,

00:02:45.280 --> 00:02:47.750 align:middle line:10%
it may be one of the most
powerful, underrated,

00:02:47.750 --> 00:02:51.560 align:middle line:10%
and perhaps hopeful messages
seen in modern times.

00:02:51.560 --> 00:02:55.700 align:middle line:84%
Because beyond the theme of
the ETs, and of the conflict,

00:02:55.700 --> 00:02:58.160 align:middle line:84%
and UFOs, and the
special effects,

00:02:58.160 --> 00:03:02.310 align:middle line:84%
what the movie is saying to
us is that there is a message.

00:03:02.310 --> 00:03:04.800 align:middle line:84%
And the message is
very, very simple.

00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:06.830 align:middle line:10%
The message says
that the language

00:03:06.830 --> 00:03:09.230 align:middle line:10%
that we use in
our everyday lives

00:03:09.230 --> 00:03:13.100 align:middle line:10%
determines the way our
brain connects the neurons

00:03:13.100 --> 00:03:15.800 align:middle line:10%
and in turn, the way
that we think and even

00:03:15.800 --> 00:03:17.770 align:middle line:10%
what we think about.

00:03:17.770 --> 00:03:20.600 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to let you think
about what I just said.

00:03:20.600 --> 00:03:24.050 align:middle line:84%
This movie is suggesting
somehow that the words

00:03:24.050 --> 00:03:28.420 align:middle line:84%
that we use to communicate
day in and day out--

00:03:28.420 --> 00:03:32.720 align:middle line:84%
they are more than simply
words, that they actually

00:03:32.720 --> 00:03:36.570 align:middle line:84%
are directly linked to
the neurons in our brain.

00:03:36.570 --> 00:03:40.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you've ever thought
about the power of just being

00:03:40.340 --> 00:03:44.330 align:middle line:84%
able to speak, I'd
like to share with you

00:03:44.330 --> 00:03:48.020 align:middle line:84%
just how potent that
ability is unto itself.

00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:52.370 align:middle line:84%
And that will lead us into the
power of the language itself.

00:03:52.370 --> 00:03:56.480 align:middle line:84%
When we speak, when we say
the words to convey what

00:03:56.480 --> 00:04:00.310 align:middle line:84%
it is that we're thinking
and feeling in our lives,

00:04:00.310 --> 00:04:02.520 align:middle line:84%
what we're really
doing is a series

00:04:02.520 --> 00:04:05.990 align:middle line:84%
of steps that begins with
one of the most intimate acts

00:04:05.990 --> 00:04:07.630 align:middle line:90%
that we could ever imagine.

00:04:07.630 --> 00:04:11.700 align:middle line:84%
We invite into the deepest
recesses of our bodies

00:04:11.700 --> 00:04:15.360 align:middle line:84%
the breath of life from the
world beyond our bodies.

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:19.220 align:middle line:84%
We breathe in what is
called the sacred breath.

00:04:19.220 --> 00:04:21.500 align:middle line:84%
We breathe it into our
bodies, and we draw

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:24.410 align:middle line:90%
it deep into our diaphragm.

00:04:24.410 --> 00:04:27.025 align:middle line:84%
And once that breath
is in the diaphragm,

00:04:27.025 --> 00:04:30.050 align:middle line:90%
we begin to massage that breath.

00:04:30.050 --> 00:04:31.610 align:middle line:10%
With our diaphragm,
with the muscles

00:04:31.610 --> 00:04:33.890 align:middle line:10%
in our diaphragm in
a very precise wave,

00:04:33.890 --> 00:04:37.460 align:middle line:10%
we flutter the diaphragm
just the right way

00:04:37.460 --> 00:04:40.430 align:middle line:10%
to now direct the air
back from where it just

00:04:40.430 --> 00:04:46.670 align:middle line:10%
came, back through the passages,
over the muscles in our throat

00:04:46.670 --> 00:04:51.500 align:middle line:10%
that vibrate and undulate in
just the right way at just

00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:54.740 align:middle line:10%
the right time to create
the acoustic vibrations that

00:04:54.740 --> 00:04:58.910 align:middle line:10%
allow what we were thinking
to be emitted from our body,

00:04:58.910 --> 00:05:02.330 align:middle line:10%
from our mouth, back
into the air around us

00:05:02.330 --> 00:05:06.080 align:middle line:10%
as messages that
become precisely that,

00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:08.150 align:middle line:10%
the messages that
are interpreted

00:05:08.150 --> 00:05:09.950 align:middle line:10%
through the eardrums
of the people

00:05:09.950 --> 00:05:11.360 align:middle line:10%
that we're speaking with.

00:05:11.360 --> 00:05:12.160 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:05:12.160 --> 00:05:14.840 align:middle line:84%
When you think about
that, what masters we are.

00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:17.405 align:middle line:84%
What masters we are
at the communication.

00:05:17.405 --> 00:05:21.080 align:middle line:84%
But what our ancestors
are telling us is that

00:05:21.080 --> 00:05:24.320 align:middle line:84%
the language that we
are using to convey

00:05:24.320 --> 00:05:27.110 align:middle line:90%
that sacred acoustic vibration--

00:05:27.110 --> 00:05:30.300 align:middle line:84%
that language is really
where the action is.

00:05:30.300 --> 00:05:32.990 align:middle line:84%
So the English language
as well as many others

00:05:32.990 --> 00:05:36.230 align:middle line:84%
is based upon principles
of separation.

00:05:36.230 --> 00:05:39.410 align:middle line:84%
And that separation is
reflected in the ideas

00:05:39.410 --> 00:05:42.020 align:middle line:84%
that it embraces,
separate and isolated

00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:47.630 align:middle line:84%
thinking about things like you
versus me or them versus us.

00:05:47.630 --> 00:05:50.370 align:middle line:84%
We think about
winners and losers.

00:05:50.370 --> 00:05:53.420 align:middle line:84%
This is the language
of conflict and war.

00:05:53.420 --> 00:05:56.060 align:middle line:84%
Language based in
connection creates

00:05:56.060 --> 00:05:58.910 align:middle line:84%
a very, very different
kind of experience,

00:05:58.910 --> 00:06:00.385 align:middle line:90%
different kind of thinking.

00:06:00.385 --> 00:06:04.160 align:middle line:84%
A language based in
connection is unity thinking.

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:06.410 align:middle line:84%
This is the language of
evolution, of community,

00:06:06.410 --> 00:06:08.095 align:middle line:90%
of cooperation.

00:06:08.095 --> 00:06:11.120 align:middle line:84%
So the bottom line to what
I'm saying to you here

00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:12.530 align:middle line:90%
is that we changed the language.

00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:13.550 align:middle line:90%
We changed the brain.

00:06:13.550 --> 00:06:18.410 align:middle line:84%
Or stated another way, change
the language, change the way

00:06:18.410 --> 00:06:21.090 align:middle line:90%
the brain accesses the matrix.

00:06:21.090 --> 00:06:24.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, these ideas are central
to the theme of the "Arrival."

00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:26.750 align:middle line:90%
And here's what I mean.

00:06:26.750 --> 00:06:29.720 align:middle line:84%
A growing body of
scientific evidence

00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:34.160 align:middle line:84%
now suggests that we
do not hold memory

00:06:34.160 --> 00:06:36.650 align:middle line:90%
in the neurons in our bodies.

00:06:36.650 --> 00:06:40.394 align:middle line:84%
We now know we have neurons in
the heart as well as the brain.

00:06:40.394 --> 00:06:41.810 align:middle line:84%
What these discoveries
are showing

00:06:41.810 --> 00:06:46.880 align:middle line:84%
us is that those neurons are
not what contain the memory,

00:06:46.880 --> 00:06:53.780 align:middle line:84%
rather the neurons we can
think of as biological antenna,

00:06:53.780 --> 00:06:58.250 align:middle line:84%
soft antenna that tune to
the place in the field,

00:06:58.250 --> 00:07:02.960 align:middle line:84%
in the matrix where our
memories actually reside.

00:07:02.960 --> 00:07:05.940 align:middle line:84%
Now, this idea is more
than just a metaphor.

00:07:05.940 --> 00:07:07.820 align:middle line:90%
It's more than just a theory.

00:07:07.820 --> 00:07:09.950 align:middle line:84%
What I'm saying
to you is so real

00:07:09.950 --> 00:07:13.190 align:middle line:84%
that engineers are
actually now beginning

00:07:13.190 --> 00:07:17.510 align:middle line:84%
to design the next generation of
computer chips based precisely

00:07:17.510 --> 00:07:19.210 align:middle line:90%
by this idea.

00:07:19.210 --> 00:07:24.230 align:middle line:84%
When engineers were working
with futuristic technologies,

00:07:24.230 --> 00:07:26.540 align:middle line:84%
they were saying, where
is our computer technology

00:07:26.540 --> 00:07:28.410 align:middle line:90%
going to go?

00:07:28.410 --> 00:07:30.200 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
they discovered

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:34.310 align:middle line:84%
is that the silica that
we've used in the past

00:07:34.310 --> 00:07:36.920 align:middle line:84%
has limitations for the
amount of information

00:07:36.920 --> 00:07:39.620 align:middle line:84%
that can be stored
on that silicon chip.

00:07:39.620 --> 00:07:42.170 align:middle line:90%
So they began looking to nature.

00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:45.770 align:middle line:84%
Where in nature can
we find the material

00:07:45.770 --> 00:07:48.320 align:middle line:84%
that could contain the
vast amounts of information

00:07:48.320 --> 00:07:50.420 align:middle line:84%
that we're now
beginning to access?

00:07:50.420 --> 00:07:52.250 align:middle line:90%
And they chose water.

00:07:52.250 --> 00:07:56.990 align:middle line:84%
The new chips are actually based
upon a single droplet of water.

00:07:56.990 --> 00:07:59.630 align:middle line:84%
Now, this isn't tap
water from the bathroom.

00:07:59.630 --> 00:08:03.950 align:middle line:84%
It's highly refined, highly
structured water compressed

00:08:03.950 --> 00:08:08.720 align:middle line:84%
into a chip that interfaces
with the machine,

00:08:08.720 --> 00:08:11.660 align:middle line:84%
with the computer
as we know it today.

00:08:11.660 --> 00:08:14.990 align:middle line:84%
When the researchers began
filling these chips with

00:08:14.990 --> 00:08:18.920 align:middle line:84%
information, what happened was
there was so much information

00:08:18.920 --> 00:08:22.490 align:middle line:84%
that was being stored, they said
this droplet of water cannot

00:08:22.490 --> 00:08:25.730 align:middle line:84%
possibly store that
amount of information.

00:08:25.730 --> 00:08:29.030 align:middle line:84%
They were pumping tremendous
amounts, libraries

00:08:29.030 --> 00:08:31.400 align:middle line:90%
of information into this chip.

00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:34.340 align:middle line:84%
And the mystery was, where's
the information being stored?

00:08:34.340 --> 00:08:37.370 align:middle line:84%
And they realized that the
information was not confined

00:08:37.370 --> 00:08:39.289 align:middle line:90%
to the droplet of water.

00:08:39.289 --> 00:08:43.760 align:middle line:84%
The information was being
held in a field that is linked

00:08:43.760 --> 00:08:44.840 align:middle line:90%
to that droplet of water.

00:08:44.840 --> 00:08:46.670 align:middle line:84%
The information
was actually being

00:08:46.670 --> 00:08:50.150 align:middle line:84%
held in a field that extended
beyond the machine itself.

00:08:50.150 --> 00:08:52.309 align:middle line:84%
I know this is a very
different way of thinking,

00:08:52.309 --> 00:08:53.350 align:middle line:90%
but this is how we learn.

00:08:53.350 --> 00:08:57.200 align:middle line:84%
This is how science arrives
at the new understandings that

00:08:57.200 --> 00:08:59.990 align:middle line:84%
lead us to deeper
understandings,

00:08:59.990 --> 00:09:02.970 align:middle line:84%
perhaps the deepest
truths of our existence.

00:09:02.970 --> 00:09:06.510 align:middle line:84%
So the information doesn't
live in our brains.

00:09:06.510 --> 00:09:07.760 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't live in our hearts.

00:09:07.760 --> 00:09:09.560 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't live in our cells.

00:09:09.560 --> 00:09:12.110 align:middle line:84%
The information is stored
in the world around us.

00:09:12.110 --> 00:09:15.590 align:middle line:84%
And because of that,
the way we access

00:09:15.590 --> 00:09:18.410 align:middle line:84%
that information plays a
very, very powerful role

00:09:18.410 --> 00:09:21.400 align:middle line:90%
in our lives.

00:09:21.400 --> 00:09:22.840 align:middle line:90%
So I'd like to share a story.

00:09:22.840 --> 00:09:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And this is a true story of
precisely what the information

00:09:27.580 --> 00:09:30.910 align:middle line:84%
I just shared with you
means in our lives.

00:09:30.910 --> 00:09:34.060 align:middle line:84%
I live in an artist community,
a very creative community

00:09:34.060 --> 00:09:36.130 align:middle line:90%
in northern New Mexico.

00:09:36.130 --> 00:09:37.420 align:middle line:90%
A lot of artists--

00:09:37.420 --> 00:09:41.270 align:middle line:84%
visual artists,
sculptors, musicians,

00:09:41.270 --> 00:09:43.602 align:middle line:84%
writers all come
together in the beauty

00:09:43.602 --> 00:09:45.310 align:middle line:84%
of the high desert of
northern New Mexico

00:09:45.310 --> 00:09:46.730 align:middle line:90%
to create what they create.

00:09:46.730 --> 00:09:47.980 align:middle line:90%
And it's always been that way.

00:09:47.980 --> 00:09:51.370 align:middle line:84%
Georgia O'Keeffe, for example,
Ansel Adams made their home.

00:09:51.370 --> 00:09:52.190 align:middle line:90%
DH Lawrence.

00:09:52.190 --> 00:09:54.356 align:middle line:84%
They all made their homes
in this part of the world,

00:09:54.356 --> 00:09:57.060 align:middle line:84%
because it supports
this creative spirit.

00:09:57.060 --> 00:09:59.230 align:middle line:84%
Well, one of the interesting
things that I've seen

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:01.100 align:middle line:84%
in my community-- and
if you're an artist,

00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:03.010 align:middle line:84%
you may have experienced
this as well--

00:10:03.010 --> 00:10:04.780 align:middle line:84%
is that a lot of
times the artists

00:10:04.780 --> 00:10:06.450 align:middle line:84%
have a hard time
supporting themselves

00:10:06.450 --> 00:10:07.450 align:middle line:90%
through their creations.

00:10:07.450 --> 00:10:10.540 align:middle line:84%
So they end up with
other jobs to make

00:10:10.540 --> 00:10:14.110 align:middle line:84%
the income that allows them
to create the things that they

00:10:14.110 --> 00:10:15.130 align:middle line:90%
love.

00:10:15.130 --> 00:10:16.838 align:middle line:84%
And the story I'm
going to share with you

00:10:16.838 --> 00:10:19.720 align:middle line:84%
is a story of precisely
such an artist.

00:10:19.720 --> 00:10:21.490 align:middle line:84%
But it relates to
the way information

00:10:21.490 --> 00:10:24.970 align:middle line:84%
is stored in the field and
what it can mean to a creation.

00:10:24.970 --> 00:10:26.470 align:middle line:90%
So I had a dear friend of mine--

00:10:26.470 --> 00:10:29.230 align:middle line:84%
musician, keyboard
artist who had just

00:10:29.230 --> 00:10:30.940 align:middle line:84%
created one of
the most awesomely

00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:35.200 align:middle line:84%
beautiful, mystical, compelling,
intriguing pieces of music

00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:36.670 align:middle line:90%
that I had ever heard.

00:10:36.670 --> 00:10:40.300 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, I can't wait
until that becomes available.

00:10:40.300 --> 00:10:45.220 align:middle line:84%
Well, to my musician friend,
it wasn't ready for the world.

00:10:45.220 --> 00:10:46.774 align:middle line:90%
He said, I like what I've done.

00:10:46.774 --> 00:10:48.940 align:middle line:84%
He said, but it's not quite
ready for the world yet.

00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:50.731 align:middle line:84%
He says, I'm going to
take it in the studio

00:10:50.731 --> 00:10:51.880 align:middle line:90%
and do some more work.

00:10:51.880 --> 00:10:53.680 align:middle line:90%
So he would go into the studio.

00:10:53.680 --> 00:10:56.590 align:middle line:84%
He'd spend all of his
money, honing and refining

00:10:56.590 --> 00:10:58.280 align:middle line:90%
this masterful piece of work.

00:10:58.280 --> 00:10:59.780 align:middle line:90%
Then he'd run out of money.

00:10:59.780 --> 00:11:02.530 align:middle line:84%
And then he would spend six
months working in a restaurant

